main event: A bright white object was observed in the sky over Calumet Park, Illinois on August 29, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be in distress, as it was not maintaining a steady northerly course.
The object was observed for about 20 minutes, from 12:35 AM to 12:55 AM.
The object was described as being about the size of a pea and brighter than any star or the moon.
The object seemed to descend and ascend at times, and disappeared instantaneously on the horizon.
No sound was heard coming from the object, and it did not appear to be a satellite or any known aircraft type.
